---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Journey - Jack Luo"
  description="A place to showcase achievements, journey throughout different fields, and creative works."
  currentPage="journey"
>
  <!-- Journey Landing Section -->
  <div slot="hero" class="landing-main container-fluid">
    <div class="row landing-row journey-container">
      <h3>Projects</h3>
      <p style="text-align: center; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8); font-style: italic; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        <a href="/projects" style="color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9); text-decoration: underline;">
          Projects have been moved to a new dedicated page â†’
        </a>
        <br/>
        <span style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);">Updated November 2025</span>
      </p>
      <!-- Hidden project cards section (preserved from original) -->
      <div class="row" style="display: none;">
        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6 col-4-lg">
          <div class="project-card">
            <h3 class="project-header">Calend.ai - AI scheduler</h3>
            <img
              src="/assets/images/projects/calendai.png"
              class="project-image"
              alt="Calend.ai project"
            />
            <p>
              <a href="https://bit.ly/calendai" class="a-underline"
                >Calend.ai</a
              > is a chrome extension that leverages modern nlp
              techniques and prompt engineering to automatically
              schedule and manage events within a user's google
              calendar. It learns behaviors of user scheduled events and
              provides personalized descriptions.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6 col-4-lg">
          <div class="project-card">
            <h3 class="project-header">
              Vigama - Automation assistant
            </h3>
            <img
              src="/assets/images/projects/vigama.gif"
              class="project-image"
              alt="Vigama project"
            />
            <p>
              <a href="https://vigama.tech" class="a-underline"
                >Vigama</a
              >
              is an AI-driven productivity app that automates low level
              tasks and generates schedule based on user preferences.
              Vigama captures language either through text or speech
              from the user and outputs both text/speech and executes
              commands.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row" style="display: none;">
        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6 col-4-lg">
          <div class="project-card">
            <h3 class="project-header">
              Lingua Scan - Computer Vision
            </h3>
            <img
              src="/assets/images/projects/linguascan.png"
              class="project-image"
              alt="Lingua Scan project"
            />
            <p>
              Developed
              <a
                href="https://github.com/thejackluo/lingua-scan"
                class="a-underline"
                >Lingua Scan</a
              >, an innovative, immersive language learning platform
              that leverages computer vision to enable dynamic and
              nuanced language learning, bringing the power of
              category-based learning, real-time object scanning and
              translation.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6 col-4-lg">
          <div class="project-card">
            <h3 class="project-header">Q Hacker House</h3>
            <img
              src="/assets/images/projects/hackerhouse.jpg"
              class="project-image"
              alt="Q Hacker House project"
            />
            <p>
              In 2023 summer, hosted a hacker house in downtown SF for 10
              people to build startups, do research, and learn from
              others. Help coordinated logistics for the house while
              created
              <a href="https://prodicity.org" class="a-underline"
                >Prodicity</a
              >
              - AI mentorship for 20+ high school students.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Creative Section -->
  <section id="creative">
    <div class="creative-container container-fluid">
      <div class="landing-main container-fluid">
        <div class="landing-row row">
          <h3>Creative</h3>
          <p>
            From July 23 and onwards, I started writing a book about a guy
            stuck in a limbinal space. In 'Limbinal,' I created a world
            where reality blurs, and boundaries between dreams and waking
            life become indistinguishable. I explore things like identity,
            the pursuit of meaning and "robotic racism". Feel free to read a
            sample
            <a class="a-underline" href="/assets/pdf/limbinal-v12.03.23.pdf">here</a>
            and let me know
            <a href="https://instagram.com/thejackluo">here</a> any
            feedbacks and questions about the book (bonus points if you know
            publishers).
            <br />
            <br />

            <b>I am currently reading</b>: the third door by Alex Banayan
            <br />
            <b>Past Reads</b>: Three Body Problem, Sapiens: A brief history of humankind, 
            The Third Door, Zero to One, How to Win Friends and Influence
            People, Where you go is not who you will be, The Future is
            Faster than you think, Subtle art of not giving a f*ck, The
            Unfair Advantage
          </p>
          <p>
            I made music since 10th grade. Most pieces are experimental, but
            I'd recommend you check out a few highlights here:
            <a
              class="a-underline"
              href="https://soundcloud.com/thejackluo/intersection"
              >intersection</a
            >,
            <a
              class="a-underline"
              href="https://soundcloud.com/thejackluo/memories-v2"
              >memory v2</a
            >,
            <a
              class="a-underline"
              href="https://soundcloud.com/thejackluo/007-mirrox"
              >007 - mirrox</a
            >
            <br />

            To see all the music I spew on the Internet, explore my
            soundcloud
            <a class="a-underline" href="https://soundcloud.com/thejackluo"
              >here</a
            >
            <br />
            <br />
            If you want some music recommendations,
            <a
              class="a-underline"
              href="https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLrrS4ML6IeMKzkGx_6o-33lMyNtH6xBdq"
              >here</a
            >
            is my work playlist.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="creative-angular-filter full">
      <div class="creative-city full"></div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Import journey-specific CSS files */
  @import url('/src/css/journey.css');
  @import url('/src/css/creative.css');

  /* Override landing section height like other pages */
  :global(#landing) {
    height: auto !important;
    min-height: auto !important;
  }

  :global(.landing-container) {
    height: auto !important;
    position: relative !important;
  }

  /* Prevent horizontal scrolling globally */
  :global(html),
  :global(body),
  :global(#fullpage) {
    max-width: 100vw;
    overflow-x: hidden;
  }

  /* Ensure all containers respect viewport width */
  :global(.container-fluid) {
    max-width: 100%;
    padding-left: 0;
    padding-right: 0;
  }

  /* Fix journey container to prevent overflow */
  .journey-container {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 100%;
    padding-left: 1rem;
    padding-right: 1rem;
    box-sizing: border-box;
    overflow-x: hidden;
  }

  /* Ensure rows don't overflow */
  :global(.row) {
    margin-left: 0;
    margin-right: 0;
    max-width: 100%;
  }

  /* Fix project cards to prevent horizontal overflow */
  .project-card {
    max-width: 100%;
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }

  .project-image {
    max-width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  /* Creative section - ensure no overflow */
  #creative {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 100vw;
    overflow-x: hidden;
  }

  .creative-container {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 100%;
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }

  /* Mobile responsiveness */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .journey-container {
      padding-left: 0.5rem;
      padding-right: 0.5rem;
    }

    :global(.landing-row) {
      margin: 1rem 0.5rem;
    }

    .project-card {
      margin: 0.5em 0;
      padding: 1em;
    }

    .creative-container {
      margin: 1em;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 576px) {
    .journey-container {
      padding-left: 0.25rem;
      padding-right: 0.25rem;
    }

    :global(.nav-container) {
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }

    :global(.nav-item) {
      padding: 0 0.5em;
    }
  }
</style>

